# deploy.env — per-host deployment identity for the service-unit installers.
#
# Copy to `deploy.env` (gitignored) ONLY if the auto-derived values are wrong.
# The installers — scripts/linux/install_systemd.sh and
# scripts/macos/install_launchd.sh — substitute these into the service-unit
# templates (systemd/*.in, launchd/*.plist.in) at install time. The repo ships
# only templates; concrete units are generated into the system location and are
# never committed. See docs/reference/configuration_sources.md.
#
# PYTHON_BIN and CONDA_ENV_BIN are ALSO consulted at runtime by
# scripts/_lib.sh:resolve_python (shared by the stack's shell scripts) —
# precedence there: $SSC_PYTHON env override > PYTHON_BIN > CONDA_ENV_BIN/python
# > derived conventional conda locations > PATH python3.
#
# Everything below is auto-derived by default; uncomment only what you override.

# --- Common ---
# REPO_ROOT   — the stanford-stroke-pacs dir (default: resolved from the installer path)
# DEPLOY_USER — the OS account the services run as (default: $SUDO_USER)
#REPO_ROOT=/opt/ssc-pacs/ssc-pacs/stanford-stroke-pacs
#DEPLOY_USER=pere

# --- Linux (systemd: scripts/linux/install_systemd.sh) ---
# DEPLOY_GROUP — primary group of DEPLOY_USER (default: `id -gn`)
# PYTHON_BIN   — python in the stack's conda env (default: probes ~/miniconda3,
#                ~/anaconda3, ~/miniforge3 for env `ssc-pacs` then `pacs`,
#                then PATH python3)
# UVICORN_BIN  — uvicorn in the same env (default: alongside PYTHON_BIN)
#DEPLOY_GROUP=pacs
#PYTHON_BIN=/home/you/miniconda3/envs/pacs/bin/python
#UVICORN_BIN=/home/you/miniconda3/envs/pacs/bin/uvicorn

# --- Linux Postgres cluster (scripts/linux/provision_postgres.sh) ---
# Cluster identity, NOT deploy identity: the cluster's OS account must be a
# dedicated system user (uid < UID_MIN), never DEPLOY_USER — see
# docs/operations/postgres_provisioning.md. The script asserts the uid class
# whatever name you pick.
# PG_OS_USER — cluster OS account (default: postgres)
# PG_BIN     — dir containing initdb/pg_ctl (default: probed; set it when more
#              than one PostgreSQL major is installed)
# PGDATA     — data directory (required to provision a new cluster; on Linux
#              this is read by provision_postgres.sh, on macOS by
#              install_launchd.sh — see below)
#PG_OS_USER=postgres
#PG_BIN=/opt/pgsql18/bin
#PGDATA=/srv/ssc-pacs/pgdata

# --- macOS (launchd: scripts/macos/install_launchd.sh) ---
# HOME_DIR      — DEPLOY_USER's home (default: dscl lookup, else /Users/$DEPLOY_USER)
# BREW_PREFIX   — Homebrew prefix (default: `brew --prefix`, else /opt/homebrew)
# CONDA_ENV_BIN — bin/ of the `ssc-pacs` conda env
#                 (default: $BREW_PREFIX/Caskroom/miniconda/base/envs/ssc-pacs/bin)
# PGDATA        — Postgres data dir (default: $BREW_PREFIX/var/postgresql@16)
#HOME_DIR=/Users/pere
#BREW_PREFIX=/opt/homebrew
#CONDA_ENV_BIN=/opt/homebrew/Caskroom/miniconda/base/envs/ssc-pacs/bin
#PGDATA=/opt/homebrew/var/postgresql@16
